</ol>

<p>This is not sequential consistency, in order to satisfy P2, Write(a) must be scheduled after Write(b), but P3 requires read(a) and then read(b). This is contradict</p>

<ol>
  <li>(b)</li>
</ol>

<p>This satisfies sequential consistency, the server could schedule as flowing:</p>

<p>w(a) r(a) w(c) r(c) w(b) r(b)</p>

<ol>
  <li>(c)</li>
</ol>

<p>This doesnâ€™t satisfy linearizability, because r(b) must between w(a) and r(a).</p>

