    <p>This is valid,</p>

    <ul>
      <li>Assume when proposal number = 1, only A1 accepts it and others didnâ€™t receive the message.</li>
      <li>Assume when proposal number = 2, only A2 accepts it and others didnâ€™t receive the message.</li>
      <li>Now, A3 is back to the line.</li>
      <li>According to <code>Paxos P2c.(b),</code> the majority(A1, A3) has the situation where A1 accept (1, a) and A3 accept nothing, and the highest-numbered proposal accepted by acceptor in this majority is (1, a), value is a.</li>
